cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.GT 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents an end-to-end learning method for chess using deep neural networks. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves training a neural network to make decisions based on input data. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves extracting high-level features from a given position. It may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training a neural network. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as it involves learning to compare two chess positions and select the more favorable one.
